			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ctalbus on Inny did a pickup Naggy raid after one grouped died trying, and most of the ppl bailed.   Round Two: Minimul buffs<BR>
<BR>
Fight :<BR>
 <BR>
Results : 1 Dead Dragon and 3 Characters perished<BR>
<BR>
Naggy might have lasted 90 seconds but that could be a stretch <BR>
<BR>
A fourth player ld'd into the lava(As it was mentioned before turn all the crap off)<BR>
<BR>
The tenth group had only four ppl in it and the total raid party had only 5 or 6 casters and 50 or more tanks<BR>
<BR>
Loot:<BR>
<BR>
Dropped Seilo's drums, Paly book, two Bags and two shammy hammers<BR>
<BR>
No drop loot was rolled first, by Paly's. Remaining loot was held by CT and group leaders as not to rot. <BR>
<BR>
Rolls where done by each group in turn and every roll was written down. The top five stepped forward to pick from the drops. It was quick, straight forward, and fair. Don't get hung up on the loot.<BR>
<BR>
One of the dead was a cleric, try this... <BR>
<BR>
Technique:<BR>
<BR>
Reverse assist to change and toggle through targets, very fast and very affective. assist your target to target the mob, then repeat to assist the mob, if it is the name of your target, don't heal yet. Let them run out and lose the top of the aggro list... if not All the clerics get summoned and slaughtered in turn for healing the mob's target.. <BR>
<BR>
The Moral:<BR>
A good leader, communication and group stategy are more efficent than buffs. <BR>
<BR>
(just to let all you ppl out their that are too picky about who you let in your group, it might matter, but it might not matter at all. Try to break out of your two dimensional thinking.  Consider it food for thought on another &quot;high-level hangup&quot; <BR>
<BR>
All in all, <BR>
Just a good ol' fashioned beatdown on a dragon<BR>
<BR>
Druid of high level<BR>
Inny<BR>
<BR>

