			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This MIGHT be THE BEST and most informational artical I've read about Everquest in four months, and that is a HUGE compliment concidering a day doesn't go by that I don't try to jump on the internet to get some info on this game. I plan to tell my guild about this article.  <BR>
 Anyone who takes offense to what Yappie has written needs to actually READ THE ARTICLE especially where it says &quot;If you don't like the way the leader is handling the raid then leave.&quot; After all there will be another raid tomorrow, next week, or next month if you don't like this raid wait and ask to join the next. If you don't like the way those are organized maybe you shouldn't go on raids. <BR>
Dieing is part of the game and yes it is actually a game, if you don't think it is ask someone who has had a loved one die in real life. <BR>
No one likes to die in the game and worse no one likes to die because one idiot couldn't listen, because of ego or because of plain stupidity. <BR>
One last thing, the way one writes, and especially the way one plays their character says alot about how that person is in real life. If you act like a jerk in the game, you probably are in real life. The better players know if you are a good player or bad, if you are a loot hog or not. <BR>
I'm not saying what is written by Yappie is 100% correct, but it gives some very good guidelines. Organizing a group of people is a tough thing to do, and it's worse when a few people want to be individuals rather than part of a group. If you don't like it leave, your other alternative is to put up with it, anything else puts you in the jerk catagory.<BR>
