	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To Reikoh Moonwhisper,<BR>
<BR>
I must wonder at your level myself.  For I find your comment about &quot;nazism&quot; to be a rather un-informed one.  <BR>
<BR>
First off, whether you agree with the original post or not, he gave you great advice.  If you don't like the way a raid is going, leave.  You can go off to do other things that may be more &quot;Fun&quot; for you.  You will doubtlessly save the raid members a headache by doing so too.... nothing is worse on a raid than one person brining down everyone else.<BR>
<BR>
Secondly, just because something is organized, and structured, how is that any less fun ?  Do you play sports ?  What sport do you play where there are no referees or rules ?  Have you ever played Monopoly ?  How about an easier game, have you ever played candyland ?  Im sure you see my point, these games and sports have rules, guidelines and mesurable and attainable goals.<BR>
<BR>
Third and finally, on the topic of how serious some people are.  Even if you are more lacksadasial about EQ than the other players around you think about this....<BR>
If you have a raid with even 30 people, and you screw things up and die, also causing the group to get wiped out.... you not only waste an hour of your own time getting your corpse back, but everyone elses.<BR>
So its not an hour of wasted time, its 30 hours wasted.... Think about that for one moment... Imagine, 30 hours down the drain, because you weren't paying attention for 5 minutes.<BR>
To put that in perspective...<BR>
Imagine for a moment that if you attend school and your teacher catches you daydreaming in class for 5 minutes he makes you attend summer school the entire summer.  For five minutes of day dreaming.<BR>
OR.....<BR>
If you are a little older....<BR>
Imagine your boss catches you playing Tetris at work, instead of berating you, he simply docks an ENTIRE WEEKS pay.<BR>
<BR>
Does that help put it into perspective a bit more ?  Because thats why people take this game seriously, you waste not just your own time when you goof around, but countless others.<BR>
<BR>
I hope what ive said here has made some sense to you, and I hope you learn a little from it.<BR>
<BR>
Be safe, see you in EQ.<BR>
<BR>
Ghesta Icepaw<BR>
Heroes officer<BR>
Luclin server
				</font>
			</td>

